Sasalin blows out a stream of flame, this tall slark person sets a small patch of forest ablaze, then circles above, observing the timing.  It is strange that when he slows down, the strange cries coming from behind also stop.  Sasalin forgot that there was a passenger on his back.
“Come on, Tenruk, you've turned into a slark person before, haven't you?”
“Being swept away by a giant pink dragon by surprise is a completely different story!”
“Good, Kayel?”
Kayel obviously disagrees with Nisi's statement, he looks paler than usual, his claws have sunk deep into Sasalin's back, causing the slark person to bleed, but Sasalin seems not to care.  Although so, Sasalin still realizes that he has scared the new friend, so he finds a vacant spot to land.
“Sorry, sorry, I caught a whiff of something. I have to handle this!”
“You had to drag us along too, didn't you?” Tenruk climbed down from Sasalin's back and slid down his tail to the ground, its voice sharp as it asked. "We've abandoned Rethvik! We've left behind that strong and fierce big guy! How's he supposed to find us?"
“He'll figure it out……” Nisi said with a dismissive tone. “Rethvik is slow to react, but not stupid.”
“Will Rethvik drive?”
Nisi blinked and turned to Tenruk. “Of course he'll drive.”
"Have you ever seen Rethvik drive a car? He doesn't have a truck like yours, nor has he ever driven a cute little car like Kayel's. He only started taking the bus to work because you always drive us to work. He only has a bicycle."
A burst of laughter interrupted them. Sasalin burst out laughing, but no one knew what he was laughing about. Sasalin took a while to calm down.
"Sorry, sorry, I just imagined something. Your big friend with a helmet, riding a children's bicycle designed for Temsen children. That image is too comical! I wish I had telepathic abilities, this idea is too interesting! I must keep it well-memorized!"
Kayel laughed as well, because he could imagine what Sasalin was thinking. "Okay, okay. But what did you smell? Why did you fly so fast?"
Sasalin hummed, flew away quickly, and then flew back, dropping a corpse in front of Nisi. It was an Orosarak, a very rare gold-white dragon-like species. But its head was missing. "Another one dead. I heard their cries, smelled their bloody scent. I must protect them, hunt down the murderer. This is Isiny's will. Those creatures are nearby."
Strong Sasalin suddenly stood still. Nisi and Kayel also stood still, their attention drawn to a hole on the edge of the open land. A giant and pitch-black creature was staring at them, making a hissing sound. The creature suddenly spread out its two pairs of enormous wings, charging forward with the target directly at Sasalin, completely disregarding the three small creatures in its way. Kayel and Tenruk barely dodged to the side, but Nisi was thrown to the ground and almost ended up on Sasalin's back.
Sasalin grabbed Nisi and flung her onto its back using its long and agile tail, then took off into the air. The black creature with two pairs of wings quickly chased after them.
Kayel clicked his tongue and pulled out a rifle from behind, then opened a bag to take out a belt of bullets. He hung the belt of bullets on his chest, making it easier to grab, but quickly realized that Nisi, Sasalin, and the monster were nowhere to be seen.
'Hey, Tenruk, can you transform into a flying animal?' Kayel asked.
'You want to chase after them?'
“Don't talk nonsense.”
“But…… one of them is a giant monster!”
“So what? This rifle of mine is powerful, and I can fire it at any moment. As long as I see it, I can shoot it down.”
Kayel hesitated for a moment, then took a step back and created some space for himself. With a low, slightly painful groan, Kayel's body stretched out and his skin turned into scales, his arms turned into wings. He quickly transformed into a normal, pale blue slark person, but his eyes remained red.
“Come on.”
Tenruk now looks like a relatively ordinary slark person, with scales neatly arranged on his back and a pair of sharp spikes, making it easier for Kayel to grab him. Tenruk took a long time to take flight, but once he soared into the air, he quickly adjusted his direction and tried to chase after them.
However, Tenruk and Kayel soon realized that they weren't the only ones they had to face. A second dark monster suddenly emerged from beneath them, and Tenruk narrowly dodged the collision.
"I guess this is the other terrifying big monster Rethvik was worried about?" Kayel furrowed his brow, trying to fire at the second monster, but missed. He quickly reloaded.
Tenruk didn't respond, he was too busy flying towards Nisi and Sasalin, despite the other monster chasing after them. Kayel awkwardly turned around, facing the monster. The monster was chasing after them, and Kayel thought this was a good thing, as he would be easier to target and shoot. Two bullets pierced the monster's upper wing, and it let out a pained howl, disappearing into the forest. Kayel wasn't sure if it was still following them, but he thought it was definitely lagging behind.
Before them, Sasalin was frantically waving his body, spewing flames at the black monster, while Nisi desperately held onto Sasalin to prevent falling off. Although this monster was definitely injured, it seemed to be enraged and unwilling to back down, and the flames seemed to have caused little damage. After Sasalin stabilized himself, Nisi seized the opportunity to pull out her trusty shotgun. Of course, the shotgun wouldn't be able to take down the monster, but the scattered bullets at least might be able to scare off the black beast?
